@startuml
title Stotra Stock Trading Simulator - Deployment Sequence

actor Developer
participant "AWS Amplify" as Amplify
participant "Frontend Build\n(Vite)" as ViteBuild
participant "AWS EC2" as EC2
participant "Backend Server\n(Node.js/Express)" as Backend
participant "MongoDB Atlas" as MongoDB
participant "External APIs\n(Yahoo/Alpha Vantage)" as ExternalAPI
participant "Cloudflare" as Cloudflare
participant "End User Browser" as Browser

== Frontend Deployment ==
Developer -> ViteBuild: npm run build
activate ViteBuild
ViteBuild -> ViteBuild: Bundle React app\nwith Vite
ViteBuild --> Developer: Build artifacts ready
deactivate ViteBuild

Developer -> Amplify: Deploy frontend build
activate Amplify
Amplify -> Amplify: Upload static assets
Amplify -> Amplify: Configure routing
Amplify -> Amplify: Setup CDN
Amplify --> Developer: Frontend deployed
deactivate Amplify

== Backend Deployment ==
Developer -> EC2: SSH connection
activate EC2
Developer -> EC2: Upload backend code
EC2 -> EC2: Install dependencies\n(npm install)

EC2 -> EC2: Configure environment\nvariables (.env)
note right
  - MongoDB connection string
  - JWT secret
  - API keys (Yahoo, Alpha Vantage)
  - Cloudflare Turnstile
end note

EC2 -> MongoDB: Test database connection
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> EC2: Connection successful
deactivate MongoDB

EC2 -> ExternalAPI: Verify API credentials
activate ExternalAPI
ExternalAPI --> EC2: APIs accessible
deactivate ExternalAPI

EC2 -> EC2: Start Node.js server\n(pm2/systemd)
EC2 -> EC2: Initialize Express app
EC2 -> EC2: Setup middleware\n(auth, rate limiting)
EC2 -> EC2: Load Swagger docs
EC2 -> EC2: Initialize node-cache

EC2 -> Cloudflare: Register with Turnstile
activate Cloudflare
Cloudflare --> EC2: Security integration active
deactivate Cloudflare

EC2 --> Developer: Backend deployed & running
deactivate EC2

== Runtime Configuration ==
Developer -> Amplify: Configure API proxy
activate Amplify
Amplify -> EC2: Set backend endpoint
activate EC2
EC2 --> Amplify: Endpoint configured
deactivate EC2
Amplify --> Developer: Proxy configured
deactivate Amplify

== User Access Flow ==
Browser -> Amplify: Request application
activate Browser
activate Amplify
Amplify --> Browser: Serve frontend (HTML/JS/CSS)
deactivate Amplify

Browser -> EC2: API requests via proxy
activate EC2
EC2 -> Cloudflare: Validate request (Turnstile)
activate Cloudflare
Cloudflare --> EC2: Request validated
deactivate Cloudflare

EC2 -> MongoDB: Query user data
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> EC2: Return data
deactivate MongoDB

EC2 -> ExternalAPI: Fetch stock data (cached)
activate ExternalAPI
ExternalAPI --> EC2: Return stock info
deactivate ExternalAPI

EC2 --> Browser: API response (JSON)
deactivate EC2
Browser -> Browser: Render UI with data
deactivate Browser

== Monitoring & Scaling ==
EC2 -> EC2: Health check endpoint
EC2 -> MongoDB: Monitor connections
activate MongoDB
MongoDB --> EC2: Connection pool status
deactivate MongoDB

note over Amplify, EC2
  AWS Amplify auto-scales frontend
  EC2 instance can be scaled manually
  or with auto-scaling groups
end note

@enduml
